### Node.js Express param() Function Instrumentation

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

This snippet shows the instrumentation of the `param()` function in Express. The Node.js agent now creates metrics and transaction segments when `param()` is invoked as part of a route. This also resolves an issue with transaction naming when the HTTP response is ended within a `param()` method.

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const app = express();
const newrelic = require('newrelic');

app.param('id', function(req, res, next, id) {
  // The New Relic agent will now instrument this param() function.
  // Metrics and transaction segments will be created for this operation.
  console.log('CALLED ');
  // If the response was ended here, the transaction naming issue is also fixed.
  // res.send('param: ' + id);
  next();
});

app.get('/user/:id', function(req, res) {
  res.send('user ' + req.params.id);
});

// When a request like GET /user/123 is made,
// the agent will track the execution of the param function.
```

