### Node.js Agent: Ignoring Transactions in Node.js

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

The New Relic Node.js agent now prevents the creation of spans on ignored transactions. Previously, spans were generated even if the transaction was marked as ignored. This change improves efficiency by not generating unnecessary data for transactions that are intentionally excluded.

```javascript
// Example of ignoring a transaction:
newrelic.agent.setIgnoreTransaction(true);

// Spans will no longer be produced for this transaction.
```

